      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You are right, it's quite broad, which is typical in these agreements. The phrase \"any and all losses, damages, liabilities...\" is designed to catch almost everything, so you must be vigilant about the *scope* of the agreement. Pay close attention to whether there are any limitations on liability, like caps on damages or exclusions for certain types of harm, which are often missing in these aggressive clauses. If your client is relying on this language without any limitations, it gives them very wide-ranging power.",
